devdoc.author: Witnet Foundation
devdoc.details: This contract enables posting requests that Witnet bridges will insert into the Witnet network. The result of the requests will be posted back to this contract by the bridge nodes too.

computeDrOutputHash(bytes).details: Computes the output hash of a request from its bytecode.

returns._0: The output hash of the request.

estimateGasCost(uint256).details: Estimate the amount of reward we need to insert for a given gas price.

params._gasPrice: The gas price for which we need to calculate the reward.

returns._0: The reward to be included for the given gas price.

isUpgradable(address).details: Verifies if the contract is upgradable.

postDataRequest(address).details: Posts a data request into the WRB in expectation that it will be relayed and resolved in Witnet with a total reward that equals to msg.value.

params._requestAddress: The request contract address which includes the request bytecode.

returns._0: The unique identifier of the data request.

readDataRequest(uint256).details: Retrieves the bytes of the serialization of one data request from the WRB.

params._id: The unique identifier of the data request.

returns._0: The result of the data request as bytes.

readDrTxHash(uint256).details: Retrieves hash of the data request transaction in Witnet.

params._id: The unique identifier of the data request.

returns._0: The hash of the DataRequest transaction in Witnet.

readGasPrice(uint256).details: Retrieves the gas price set for a specific DR ID.

params._id: The unique identifier of the data request.

returns._0: The gas price set by the request creator.

readResult(uint256).details: Retrieves the result (if already available) of one data request from the WRB.

params._id: The unique identifier of the data request.

reportResult(uint256,uint256,bytes).details: Reports the result of a data request in Witnet.

params._drTxHash: The unique hash of the request.
params._id: The unique identifier of the data request.

requestsCount().details: Returns the number of data requests in the WRB.

returns._0: the number of data requests in the WRB.

upgradeDataRequest(uint256).details: Increments the reward of a data request by adding the transaction value to it.

params._id: The unique identifier of the data request.
